resources.description:
## CONTRIBUTING
### Add a Shared Link
A place to record any links you share, through Forums, Emails, Chat, whatever.

Then, using the [Insomnia Plugins](todo) listed below we can **Send All Request in a Folder**
and check their response codes either `200 OK` or `301 Redirect` appropriately.

### Insomnia Test Suite
We can also write a [Insomnia Test Suite] to check those.
I find that takes too much time for such simple tests though.

### TestCafe E2E Desktop & Headless Real-Browser Testing with JS

> # End-to-end testing, simplified
> 
> No WebDriver required. No manual timeouts needed. Cross-browser testing out-of-the-box.
> 
> Free and Open Source
>
> -- https://testcafe.io/#header



If I am going to be doing tests, personally, I'll open up [TestCafe](https://www.testcafe.io) at that point and use it to run **[End-to-End] (`E2E`) Tests**, beit quick **Smoke Tests** as in the case of **links shared anywhere** (forums, social media, emails, instant message, printed short codes, generated QR codes, etc.)  **drive real _as-in-your-installed-browser-with-some-javascript-injected-real_ Web Browser Instances**, with nice and clean empty profiles (or you can defined an existing one if you want to preload your browser test with something, such as extensions). In the default case, where **TestCafe** uses a new testing profile, it is super nice to not have my extensions, my cookies (🤔 `*` _Kicked off nearly 60 minute introspective, with idea for 2FA, moved to end of this description `*`), ...



So easy to create a quick **Smoke Test** and grow it into a full-featured **Test Fixture/Suite** that can be ran in a **CI/CD Pipeline**, or, a **Developer's Automated Build Workflow**, or simply/easily/know-excel-you-can-create-and-run-tests use the lovely official [IDE], 
**[TestCafe Studio](https://www.devexpress.com/products/testcafestudio/)**.


**Well-deserved USD$250 or `TestCafe Studio Pro` for $500 w/ `DevExpress (company behind TC who generously made it [Open Source] 👍) Technical Support` and 12 months of updates.




---

### `*`
 which would void the testing anyways, but good way to preload 2FA tokens maybe with a `SMS => Web Service (Twillio?) which an existing `npm` package could listen to (`Apache Kafka?` twillio likely has a connector), do the whole thing serverless with the AWS Serverless alternative that provides _monthly free minutes_,

1. `Website` sends SMS for 2FA to **User's Registered Phone Number (RegisteredNumber)**
2. `RegisteredNumber => Twillio`
3. ~~Twillio notifies our app, or our~~ **local app polls Twillio** (better b/c local app will go up and down with the test start/stopping. + We can use `.env` for the Twillio API Credentials - #sweet)

---







---
## Idea! 💡 2FA with `Twillio` and an `npm` package to get and parse messages into 2FA codes.


### Question: Does Twillio have an API/way of parsing 2FA codes from texts?

### Q: Does Twillio have free tier? Enough for most personal/SMB use cases?
